## Connection to CPP Farm Store

Building Little Legs Pet Co. from scratch has direct parallels to the CPP Farm Store consulting project. Both are niche, mission-driven retail concepts with a passionate but under served customer base rather than a mass-market one. Little Legs serves dachshund owners who feel overlooked by mainstream pet retail, just as the CPP Farm Store serves students and community members looking for a local, education-driven alternative to chain grocery stores. Going through the exercise of defining a target customer, narrowing a product category plan, and setting up a Shopify storefront has clarified how important it is to make early, deliberate choices about *who* the store is for before deciding *what* it sells or *how* it's merchandised online. For the Farm Store project, this reinforces the value of segment-specific product positioning (e.g., highlighting CPP-grown wine and gift boxes for community members vs. convenience and discounts for students) and the importance of a clean, easy-to-navigate online storefront to convert digital discovery into real foot traffic or online orders.

